---

## Granularity iron rule: 1 PRD item = 1 row (no aggregation)

Every **smallest independently-verifiable unit** in the PRD must occupy its own row. **No merging, no summarizing.**

- ❌ Wrong (aggregated): `User CRUD API` → glossed over in one row
- ✅ Right (split out): `POST /users`, `GET /users/:id`, `PATCH /users/:id`, `DELETE /users/:id` each get a row

**Why**: aggregation makes "3 of 4 endpoints done" look like "✅ done", and the missing one never gets found. One row per item leaves gaps nowhere to hide.

**Deciding the smallest unit** (by PRD section type):
- endpoint granularity → one HTTP method + path = one row
- table granularity → one table = one row (drill down into field rows when there are many columns)
- field granularity → one field (incl. type / required / constraints) = one row
- page granularity → one screen / route = one row

