## Auto-expand (optional)

Splitting the PRD item by item by hand is tedious and error-prone. Use `scripts/expand_checklist.example.py` to auto-generate this table's skeleton from the PRD:

```bash
python scripts/expand_checklist.example.py <path/to/PRD.md> > prd-checklist.md
```

It scans PRD sections, extracts endpoint / table / field / page level smallest units, and emits a to-fill table **one item per row** (status defaults to ⬜, `verified-in-codebase?` defaults to `no`). After generation, still review manually: auto-splitting may miss requirements scattered in prose paragraphs.

